	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> <date>16 March&#47;54</date></p>
				<p>My dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed the remainder of the Translation.<lb/>  I am not quite certain if any portion I now send you<lb/> is already in yr possession&#8212;nor yet if in the first part<lb/> I used the <del>or</del> English &#8220;you&#44;&#8221; or stick to the oriental<lb/> &#8220;thou&#8221; as I have done in this secd. Half.&#8212;I do not<lb/> care which it is&#44; so that it seems<add>&#63;</add> alike thro&#39; the<lb/> whole translation&#8212;</p>
				<p>In yr place I would not displace any thing relating<lb/> to <persName>Judah Touro</persName>&#44; to make room for this Translation.<lb/>  It will <hi rend="underline">keep</hi> till next month.  But <add>in any case</add> before you see<lb/> to press have the grandeness to let one see a proof.<lb/>  I have in the former portion used &#8220;vision&#8221; for<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add>.  Upon second thought I think &#8220;revelation&#8221; is better.  Please substitute it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I trust you will not fail us on <date>Thursday</date> next<lb/> ply<add>&#63;</add>.  According to present appearances it will be the<lb/> crowning to do of the year.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Yours very truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Mr Raphale</persName></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Ph.</p>
				<p>P.S. If you send me a proof I will<lb/> return it without fail the same day that<lb/> I receive it.</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><hi rend="underline">Paid<lb/></hi></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><placeName>371 Walnut St.</placeName></p>
